Imagine waking up to a massive hole on your front lawn, that threatens to swallow your house, and has already almost sucked in your vehicle?Residents of Cheltenham Township in Montgomery County, Pennsylvania had just that experience.A massive sinkhole opened up in the front yard of a residential property in the early hours of Wednesday morning.Emergency personnel estimate it to be approximately six metres deep (20 ft) and nine metres wide (30ft).The cause of the sinkhole is not yet apparent but is reportedly under investigation. No injuries were reported.READ: The lowdown on sinkholes*Watch the video clip posted to the Wochit platform on YouTube, in the gallery above.- YouTube.com/Wochit News 